history.content: There is an error in the system right now. Hoping to get it fixed soon

children.subject: Actually, just realized an email was sent about this. It's a glitch with Cal Central, and apparently, waitlisting, and then waiting for the list to be processed solves the problem.
Also getting the same error; any word on if/when this will get fixed? Do we have to push enrolling in 189 until phase 2?

history.content:
I get the following error when trying to enroll in CS 189:

"Error: You are unable to enroll in this class at this time. Available seats are reserved and you do not meet the reserve capacity requirements. If a wait list is available, you may still be placed on the waitlist for this class. To do this, select Add Another Class to return to step 1. Select the class link, select the wait list option and resubmit your request."

I am not sure why I am getting this error, as I am a declared CS and Applied Math Major. Also there are plenty of seats available in this class.

Edit: I tried to add CS 188 and CS 162 and I got the same error. So it seems like I can't add any CS class right now. Any suggestions on what to do?
